  "text": "The xDS v3 transport protocol in Envoy v1.31.2 is implemented through a unified template-based architecture located in the Config::XdsMux namespace within source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/xds_mux/. \n\nThe core design uses a template GrpcMuxImpl<S,F,RQ,RS> defined in grpc_mux_impl.h that manages subscriptions and gRPC stream multiplexing. This template is parametrized by: S (subscription state type), F (subscription state factory), RQ (request type), and RS (response type). Two concrete specializations are created: GrpcMuxSotw for State-of-the-World using DiscoveryRequest/DiscoveryResponse, and GrpcMuxDelta for Delta mode using DeltaDiscoveryRequest/DeltaDiscoveryResponse.\n\nSubscription state is managed through the BaseSubscriptionState<RS,RQ> template (subscription_state.h), with two concrete implementations: SotwSubscriptionState (sotw_subscription_state.h) for SotW protocol state tracking, and DeltaSubscriptionState (delta_subscription_state.h) for Delta protocol state tracking. Each maintains per-type_url protocol state.\n\nThe GrpcSubscriptionImpl adapter in grpc_subscription_impl.h bridges between typed Subscription interfaces and the untyped GrpcMux, handling per-xDS API stats and logging. GrpcCollectionSubscriptionImpl provides specialization for collection-based subscriptions.\n\nThe factory pattern is implemented through GrpcConfigSubscriptionFactory, DeltaGrpcConfigSubscriptionFactory, and AdsConfigSubscriptionFactory (grpc_subscription_factory.h/cc) which select between SotW and Delta implementations based on the runtime feature flag \"envoy.reloadable_features.unified_mux\". When enabled, these factories instantiate unified GrpcMuxSotw/GrpcMuxDelta; otherwise, they use legacy GrpcMuxImpl/NewGrpcMuxImpl implementations.\n\nThe call chain flows from factories creating subscriptions, which instantiate the appropriate GrpcMux variant, which internally creates the corresponding SubscriptionState instances via their factories. The template specializations in xds_mux/grpc_mux_impl.cc explicitly instantiate both GrpcMuxImpl<DeltaSubscriptionState,DeltaSubscriptionStateFactory,...> and GrpcMuxImpl<SotwSubscriptionState,SotwSubscriptionStateFactory,...> to support both transport modes within the unified architecture."
}

